ss you write it'),(1130,'Pergunta do dia: 314','RUqROWOtcFQ','Ari Stopassola Junior','2011-06-27 03:27:19','What is the output of the following PHP script?&lt;?php\r\n$a = 1;\r\n$b = 2.5;\r\n$c = 0xFF;\n$d = $b + $c;\r\n$e = $d * $b;\r\n$f = ($d + $e) % $a;\nprint ($f + $e);\r\n?&gt;\nA: 643.75\r\nB: 432\r\nC: 643\r\nD: 257\r\nE: 432.75'),(1131,'Pergunta do dia: 312','1hvIACK5x0o','Ari Stopassola Junior','2011-06-27 03:25:31','Which of the following could result in resource starvation?\r\n(Choose 2)A: Using too little RAM\r\nB: Using a connection capable of low bandwidth only\r\nC: Increasing virtual memory beyond 2GB\r\nD: Allowing too many web server processes to run at the same time\r\nE: None of the above\nObs.: essa é a de sábado.'),(1132,'Pergunta do dia: 311','IqBfEGryXrE','Ari Stopassola Junior','2011-06-24 09:26:11','Consider the following PHP script:&lt;?php\r\nfunction get_socket($host, $port) {\r\n  $fr = fsockopen($host, $port);\r\n  stream_set_blocking($fr, false);\r\n  return $fr;\r\n}\n// Assume $host1, $host2, etc are defined properly\r\n$write_map[] = array(\'fr\' =&gt; get_socket($host1, $port1),\r\n                     \'data\' =&gt; str_pad(\"\", 500000, \"A\"));\r\n$write_map[] = array(\'fr\' =&gt; get_socket($host2, $port2),\r\n                     \'data\' =&gt; str_pad(\"\", 500000, \"B\"));\r\n$write_map[] = array(\'fr\' =&gt; get_socket($host3, $port3),\r\n                     \'data\' =&gt; str_pad(\"\", 500000, \"C\"));\ndo {\r\n  $write_sockets = array();\n  foreach($write_map as $data) {\r\n    $write_sockets[] = $data[\'fr\'];\r\n  }\n  $num_returned = stream_select($r = null, $write_sockets, $e = null, 30);\n  if($num_returned) {\r\n    foreach($write_sockets as $fr) {\r\n      foreach($write_map as $index =&gt; $data) {\r\n        if($data[\'fr\'] === $fr) {\r\n          $len = fwrite($fr, $data[\'buf\']);\n          if($len) {\r\n            $data[\'buf\'] = substr($data[\'buf\'], $len);\n            if(empty($data[\'buf\'])) {\r\n              fclose($data[\'fr\']);\n              unset($write_map[$index]);\r\n            }\r\n          }\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n} while(??????????);\r\n?&gt;\nWhat should go in the ??????? above for this script to function properly?\nA: $num_returned &gt; 0\r\nB: $len &gt; 0\r\nC: !empty($data[\'buf\'])\r\nD: count($write_sockets)\r\nE: count($write_map)'),(1133,'Pergunta do dia: 308','iubCq3gntTU','Ari Stopassola Junior','2011-06-21 08:27:16','Consider the following PHP script:&lt;?php\r\nfunction get_socket($host, $port) {\r\n  $fr = fsockopen($host, $port);\r\n  stream_set_blocking($fr, false);\r\n  return $fr;\r\n}\n// Assume $host1, $host2, etc are defined properly\r\n$write_map[] = array(\'fr\' =&gt; get_socket($host1, $port1),\r\n                     \'data\' =&gt; str_pad(\"\", 500000, \"A\"));\r\n$write_map[] = array(\'fr\' =&gt; get_socket($host2, $port2),\r\n                     \'data\' =&gt; str_pad(\"\", 500000, \"B\"));\r\n$write_map[] = array(\'fr\' =&gt; get_socket($host3, $port3),\r\n                     \'data\' =&gt; str_pad(\"\", 500000, \"C\"));\ndo {\r\n  $write_sockets = array();\n  foreach($write_map as $data) {\r\n    $write_sockets[] = $data[\'fr\'];\r\n  }\n  $num_returned = stream_select($r = null, $write_sockets, $e = null, 30);\n  if($num_returned) {\r\n    foreach($write_sockets as $fr) {\r\n      foreach($write_map as $index =&gt; $data) {\r\n        if($data[\'fr\'] === $fr) {\r\n          $len = fwrite($fr, $data[\'buf\']);\n          if($len) {\r\n            $data[\'buf\'] = substr($data[\'buf\'], $len);\n            if(empty($data[\'buf\'])) {\r\n              fclose($data[\'fr\']);\n              unset($write_map[$index]);\r\n            }\r\n          }\r\n        }\r\n      }\r\n    }\r\n  }\r\n} while(??????????);\r\n?&gt;\nWhat should go in the ??????? above for this script to function properly?\nA: $num_returned &gt; 0\r\nB: $len &gt; 0\r\nC: !empty($data[\'buf\'])\r\nD: count($write_sockets)\r\nE